pomProject.name: Apache Commons Codec
pomProject.description: The Apache Commons Codec package contains simple encoder and decoders for various formats such as Base64 and Hexadecimal.  In addition to these widely used encoders and decoders, the codec package also maintains a collection of phonetic encoding utilities.

pomProject.name: Apache Commons Logging
pomProject.description: Apache Commons Logging is a thin adapter allowing configurable bridging to other, well known logging systems.

pomProject.name: Apache FontBox
pomProject.description: The Apache FontBox library is an open source Java tool to obtain low level information from font files. FontBox is a subproject of Apache PDFBox.

pomProject.name: Apache PDFBox
pomProject.description: The Apache PDFBox library is an open source Java tool for working with PDF documents.

pomProject.name: Apache PDFBox Debugger
pomProject.description: The Apache PDFBox library is an open source Java tool for working with PDF documents. This artefact contains the PDFDebugger.

pomProject.name: Apache PDFBox tools
pomProject.description: The Apache PDFBox library is an open source Java tool for working with PDF documents. This artefact contains commandline tools using Apache PDFBox.

pomProject.name: rome
pomProject.description: All Roads Lead to ROME. ROME is a set of Atom/RSS Java utilities that make it easy to work in Java with most syndication formats. Today it accepts all flavors of RSS (0.90, 0.91, 0.92, 0.93, 0.94, 1.0 and 2.0), Atom 0.3 and Atom 1.0 feeds. Rome includes a set of parsers and generators for the various flavors of feeds, as well as converters to convert from one format to another. The parsers can give you back Java objects that are either specific for the format you want to work with, or a generic normalized SyndFeed object that lets you work on with the data without bothering about the underlying format.

pomProject.name: Apache XmpBox
pomProject.description: The Apache XmpBox library is an open source Java tool that implements Adobe's XMP(TM) specification. It can be used to parse, validate and create xmp contents. It is mainly used by subproject preflight of Apache PDFBox. XmpBox is a subproject of Apache PDFBox.
